# Web Pentesting Lab – 2026

## Description
This project presents a personal web penetration testing laboratory conducted in a controlled environment for cybersecurity training and skill development purposes.

## Objectives
- Perform vulnerability scanning on web applications
- Identify common security weaknesses
- Simulate network attacks in a safe lab environment
- Analyze captured network traffic
- Provide remediation recommendations

## Tools Used
- Nmap
- Wireshark
- SQLMap
- Acunetix
- Ettercap

## Vulnerabilities Tested
- SQL Injection
- Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- Server misconfigurations
- Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) attack simulation

## Methodology
1. Target reconnaissance
2. Vulnerability scanning
3. Exploitation simulation
4. Network traffic analysis
5. Security recommendations

## Results
- Identification of common web vulnerabilities
- Packet capture and traffic inspection
- Risk prioritization
- Practical mitigation recommendations

## Lab Environment
Personal isolated lab environment (Kali Linux + vulnerable virtual machines).

## Disclaimer
This project was conducted in a controlled lab environment strictly for educational purposes.
